A second type is known as line pump which has a slower volume, but is able to enter into the places in which a boom rig won't fit. These pump concrete into such jobs as doing ground slabs or pools, even sidewalks.

If there have been ever this like a marvel of inventions, these concrete pumping machines make it possible to complete construction jobs that would otherwise take decades and an endless supply of money to accomplish. Most of the roadways in major cities are a result of the use of concrete pumping technology. Large skyscrapers will also be being constructed with using concrete pumping advancements, and farmers who need a brand new silo are becoming so now, all with the practical utilization of these rigs that may pump concrete to vertical heights.